Syngenta names Univar exec Fyrwald as CEO from June 1
Wednesday,  4 May 2016 |  1:16  AM ETReuters



SHARES












  
Tim Boyle| Bloomberg | Getty Images
Incoming Syngenta CEO Erik Fyrwald


  Swiss agrichemicals group Syngenta on Wednesday named J. Erik Fyrwald, chief executive of U.S. chemistry distribution company Univar Inc, as CEO from June 1. He succeeds John Ramsay, who has been ad interim CEO since November 2015. 
Fyrwald spent 27 years at DuPont. In 2008, he was named head of Nalco, a provider of water treatment and oil and gas products and services. He became CEO of Univar in May 2012, Syngenta said in a statement. 






 










