Management Team






Stephen D. Newlin
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
Mr. Newlin joined Univar in May 2016 as President and Chief Executive Officer. In November 2016, he was appointed Chairman of the Board of Directors for Univar.  He previously served as Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer of PolyOne Corporation from 2006-2014, and Executive Chairman of the Board until 2016. From 2003 to 2006, Mr. Newlin was President, Industrial Sector at Ecolab, Inc. He previously spent 24 years at Nalco Chemical Company in positions of increasing responsibility, and served as President and Director of Nalco from 1998 to 2001, and was President, Chief Operating Officer, and Vice Chairman from 2000 to 2001. In addition to his election to the Univar Board of Directors in 2014, Mr. Newlin currently serves on the boards of directors of The Chemours Company and Oshkosh Corporation. Mr. Newlin holds a bachelor’s degree in civil engineering from the South Dakota School of Mines & Technology, and has completed the Tuck Executive Program at Dartmouth College and the Harvard Business School’s Advanced Management Program. He also served as a commissioned officer in the U.S. Public Health Service, earning an accelerated promotion.
Back to top





David Jukes 
President and Chief Operating Officer
Mr. Jukes joined Univar in 2002 and has served as Executive Vice President and President of Univar USA since June 2016, and President of Latin America (LATAM) since September 2015. From 2011 to 2016, Mr. Jukes served as President of Univar EMEA. From July 2009 to January 2011 he served as Vice President, Sales and Marketing EMEA, and from April 2004 to June 2009 as Regional Director of Univar UK, Ireland, the Nordics and Distrupol. Prior to joining Univar, Mr. Jukes was Senior Vice President of Global Sales, Marketing and Industry Relations, for Omnexus, a plastics industry consortium e-commerce platform. Mr. Jukes is a graduate of the London Business School.
Back to top





Carl J. Lukach
Executive Vice President, Chief Financial Officer
Mr. Lukach joined Univar in December 2014 as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. He successfully led the financial aspects of Univar’s IPO in June 2015, and the subsequent refinancing of the company’s debt, which extended maturities and reduced annual interest expense by $100 million. Before joining Univar, he held a number of senior financial and commercial leadership positions at E.I. DuPont de Nemours & Company, Inc., including President, DuPont Asia Pacific from 2008 – 2012. Mr. Lukach began his career at PricewaterhouseCoopers, where he worked in auditing and tax advisory services. He holds a bachelor’s degree in finance from Lehigh University, a master’s degree in taxation from Widener University, and is a Certified Public Accountant.
Back to top





Jeffrey W. Carr
Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary
Mr. Carr joined Univar in May 2017 as Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary. Prior to joining Univar, Mr. Carr built up more than 35 years of legal experience, most recently as President of ValoremNext LLC. Prior to that role, Mr. Carr was Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary of FMC Technologies, Inc., where he held various roles with increasing responsibility since 1993. He holds a bachelor’s degree in government and foreign affairs from the University of Virginia and a juris doctor from Georgetown University Law Center.
Back to top





Eric Foster
Senior Vice President, Chief Information Officer
Mr. Foster is Univar’s Chief Information Officer. He joined the company in 2016 with more than 20 years of information technology experience, including leading efforts to accelerate the adoption of cloud computing, mobile applications and digital platforms to enable growth and create competitive advantage. Previously, Mr. Foster served as Senior Vice President and Chief information Officer of Baxalta Inc., the $6 billion global biopharmaceutical spin off from Baxter International. Mr. Foster held a number of executive-level IT roles with Baxter International Inc. and GE Capital/Heller Financial and also served as Chief Technology Officer for Publicis Groupe. He started his career at Andersen Consulting (now Accenture) where he delivered advanced technology solutions to clients across an array of industries. Mr. Foster received a bachelor’s degree in aeronautical and astronautical engineering from the University of Illinois.
Back to top





Ian L. Gresham
Chief Marketing Officer
Mr. Gresham joined Univar in March 2017 as Chief Marketing Officer. Before Univar, Mr. Gresham was Senior Vice President of Marketing for the Diversified Brands division of Sherwin-Williams Co., where he oversaw brand, product and channel management for a number of the company’s top consumer brands. He joined Sherwin-Williams in April 2013 as Vice President of Marketing for Diversified Brands, Paint & Sundries. Mr. Gresham has also held leadership roles of increasing responsibility in product and channel marketing with Apex Tool Group, Danaher and Black & Decker. Prior to beginning his commercial career, Mr. Gresham served as a sergeant in the United States Marine Corps. He received his bachelor’s degree in business administration from the University of Maryland and a master’s degree in business administration from Harvard Business School.
Back to top





Mike Hildebrand
President, Canada, Agriculture and Environmental Sciences
Mr. Hildebrand joined Univar in 1991 and has served as President of Canada, Global Agriculture and Environmental Sciences (AGES) since October 2014. In this role, he has been responsible for developing industry strategies, growing AGES’ North American business, and identifying new geographical expansion opportunities. From December 2010 to January 2013, Mr. Hildebrand served as Vice President of Human Resources, Canada, and was General Manager of Univar’s Alberta operations from December 2006 to November 2011. Mr. Hildebrand holds a bachelor’s degree in business administration and education from the University of Calgary.
Back to top





Nick Powell
President, Europe, The Middle East, and Africa (EMEA) and Asia Pacific (APAC)
Mr. Powell is President of EMEA and APAC for Univar. He is an industry veteran with nearly 30 years in the chemical industry. He joined Univar in 2009, establishing the company’s Middle East & Africa businesses and grew its footprint including by leading the acquisition of our Turkey business. In 2014, Mr. Powell assumed leadership of EMEA’s Focused Industries where he has taken those businesses to new growth levels. In addition to EMEA, he continues to lead Univar’s APAC operations, which he successfully returned to profitability after assuming their leadership in late 2015. Prior to joining Univar, Mr. Powell has spent more than 20 years in the chemicals industry, primarily in the water treatment chemicals and construction chemicals fields. 
Back to top





Marco A. Quirino
President, Latin America
Mr. Quirino joined Univar in May 2013 as President of Univar Brazil, and has served as President of Latin America since September 2014. Mr. Quirino is responsible for all of Univar’s operations in Latin America, including driving growth strategy, strengthening relationships with suppliers, and further building Univar’s customer base. Prior to Univar, Mr. Quirino lead commercial and industrial operations at Braskem, Brazil’s leading petrochemical manufacturer with operations in Brazil, Latin America, U.S., Europe, and Asia. He previously served as Vice President of Industrial and Commercial Operations with Quattor, a large petrochemical manufacturer in Brazil, and spent 20 years with Dow Chemical in various management roles. Mr. Quirino earned his bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering from Mackenzie University and his M.B.A. from the FIA Business School. He has also completed advanced management programs at the Wharton School of Business and INSEAD.
Back to top





Dianna G. Sparacino
Vice President, Global Human Resources
Ms. Sparacino joined Univar in April 2014 as Vice President of Compensation and Benefits, and has served as our Vice President of Global Human Resources since November 2015. From October 2009 to March of 2014, Ms. Sparacino served as Vice President Global Compensation and Benefits at Molex Incorporated, a leading global supplier of electronic components and solutions. Prior to that, Ms. Sparacino held multiple roles of increasing responsibility and gained broad experience in developing and managing global compensation and benefit, talent, and career planning programs for Molex. From July 1990 to August 1999, Ms. Sparacino was responsible for the management of comprehensive benefits programs at Stepan Company, a global manufacturer of specialty chemicals. Ms. Sparacino holds a bachelor’s degree in government from the University of Notre Dame, and holds an M.B.A. in finance and organizational behavior from the Northwestern University Kellogg School of Management.
Back to top





George J. Fuller
Senior Vice President, USA Local Chemical Distribution
Mr. Fuller joined Univar in April 2013 and has served as Executive Vice President of Global Sourcing and Basic Chemicals since April 2015. From November 2012 to February 2013, Mr. Fuller was Executive Vice President of Hydrite Chemical Co., a leading provider of chemicals and related services in North America. He also held numerous other leadership roles at Hydrite, including Vice President, Sales and Procurement, as well positions in product management, procurement, and business management. Earlier in his career, Mr. Fuller was a top Sales Director and General Manager for Prillaman Chemical Corporation, a Division of Ellis & Everard. He holds a bachelor’s degree in business and marketing from Marshall University.
Back to top





Jennifer A. McIntyre
Senior Vice President, Supply Chain Operations
Ms. McIntyre joined Univar in June 2013 as Vice President of Regional Supply Chain and has led our Supply Chain and Transportation operations since December 2014. Ms. McIntyre has 26 years of experience in the chemical manufacturing industry and served in several senior leadership positions at Rohm and Haas, a subsidiary of The Dow Chemical Company that manufactures specialty chemicals, and with The Dow Chemical Company, one of the world’s largest chemical manufacturers. Most recently, Ms. McIntyre served as Global Supply Chain Director at The Dow Chemical Company from January 2010 to June 2013. Ms. McIntyre earned her bachelor’s degree in chemical engineering from Drexel University and holds an M.S. degree in environmental engineering also from Drexel University.
Back to top





Greg Vas Nunes
Senior Vice President, Digital & Customer Experience
Mr. Vas Nunes joined Univar in October 2013 as Vice President of ChemCare and Chemical Manufacturing, and has served as President, USA Specialty Products and Services, and ChemPoint since April 2015. Prior to joining Univar, Mr. Vas Nunes served as President, Europe, for Performance Fibers, a global producer of industrial polyester fibers and fabrics, from February 2011 to September 2013, and Executive Vice President of LG Hausys, a subsidiary of LG Chem, Ltd., from January 2010 to February 2011. Mr. Vas Nunes has held executive leadership roles at LG Surfaces LLC, the Spandex Performance Unit of Hyosung Corporation, and INVISTA/DuPont, one of the world’s largest integrated producers of chemical intermediates, polymers, and fibers. He holds a bachelor’s degree in Chemical Engineering from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute.
Back to top





Kerri A. Howard
Vice President, Treasurer 
Ms. Howard joined Univar in June 2011 as Assistant Treasurer, Corporate Finance and has served as our Vice President, Treasurer since September 2013. From July 2009 to June 2011, she served as Assistant Treasurer at Stryker, a leading medical technology company. Ms. Howard has over 20 years of experience in finance, including several management roles at Republic Services, Inc., an industry-leader in U.S. recycling and non-hazardous solid waste, and FINOVA Capital Corporation, a commercial financing organization. Ms. Howard holds a bachelor’s degree in finance from University of Arizona and an M.B.A from Arizona State University.
Back to top





Lynn Burgener
Vice President, Corporate Taxation
Ms. Burgener joined Univar in April 2007 and serves as our  Vice President of Corporate Taxation and is responsible for all global income tax matters for the company. From August 2000 to March 2007, Ms. Burgener held the lead tax position for the North American operations of the HeidelbergCement Group, one of the world’s largest building materials companies, with operations in 40 countries. From May 1994 to July 2000, Ms. Burgener held the lead global tax position for Exide Technologies, one the world’s largest producers, distributors, and recyclers of lead-acid batteries, with operations in 80 countries. Prior to that, she was a tax manager with KPMG LLP. Ms. Burgener is a member of the American Society of Certified Public Accountants and the Tax Executives Institute. She holds a bachelor’s degree in accounting from Arizona State University and a master’s degree in taxation from Villanova University. Ms. Burgener is a Certified Public Accountant licensed in the state of California.
Back to top



 

















